== Notes == <div class="references-small"> '''note 1.''' {{Note_label|1|note 1|none}} fur is defined by the [[Oxford English Dictionary]] as "the short, soft hair of certain animals"<ref>{{cite web|author=Askoxford.com |url=http://www.askoxford.com/80/concise_oed/fur?view=uk |title=Oxford Dictionaries, Ask Oxford - fur |publisher=Askoxford.com |date= |accessdate=2010-01-18}}</ref> whereas hair is defined as "any of the fine thread-like strands growing from the skin of mammals and other animals, or from the epidermis of a plant."<ref>{{cite web|author=Askoxford.com |url=http://www.askoxford.com/concise_oed/hair?view=uk |title=Oxford Dictionaries, Ask Oxford - hair |publisher=Askoxford.com |date= |accessdate=2010-01-18}}</ref> </div>
